OL,6,FShe asked: "What support would there
OL,7,Fbe for a business like mine to make
OL,8,Fsure the additional cost from
OL,9,Fincreasing employee national insurance
OL,10,Fcontributions aren't passed on to
OL,11,Fworking families?"
OL,13,FEmployers got it from both barrels
OL,14,Fwhen it comes to National Insurance.
OL,15,FIt's going up by 1.2% to 15% and the
OL,16,Fthreshold where it kicks in is falling
OL,17,Ffrom just over #9,000 to #5,000, both
OL,18,Ffrom next April.
